;s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1989:\"<p><img src=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/adrotate-pro-network.png\" alt=\"adrotate-pro-network\" width=\"260\" height=\"287\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-11737\" />Over the past month I&#8217;ve been monitoring responses to the new multisite support in AdRotate and some were kind enough to share some of their ideas to make the <a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/shop/adrotate-plugin/adrotate-pro-network/\" title=\"AdRotate Pro (Network)\">Network License for AdRotate Pro</a> more valuable.</p>\n<p>The next version will include a number of changes to make your networked advert campaigns more useful:</p>\n<h3>Changelog</h3>\n<div class=\"shortcode-unorderedlist arrow\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>[new] Shortcodes can now show ads from other sites when network activated </li>\n<li>[new] PHP snippets can now show ads from other sites when network activated </li>\n<li>[new] Widgets can now show ads from other sites when network activated</li>\n<li>[fix] Save redirect not always correct for network activated setups</li>\n<li>[tweak] Improved compatibility for multisite</li>\n</ul>\n<p></div>\n\n<p>Check out the <a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/development/\" title=\"Development\">developer page</a> for the full changelog.</p>\n<p>This basically means you can add adverts from your primary site (or any site) in other networked sites.</p>\n<p>This for example can be simply same user advert sharing but also you hardcoding adverts into the themes of your users with AdRotate Pro Supported features and managing the whole thing from your primary or designated site.</p>\n<p>A lot is possible&#8230; </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/making-the-network-license-more-useful/\">Making the Network License more useful</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com\">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/7bbY7gqVmwE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:82:\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/making-the-network-license-more-useful/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/making-the-network-license-more-useful/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"Push Notifications coming to AdRotate Pro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~3/9zNRDQhu7uU/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/push-notifications-coming-to-adrotate-pro/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\"