/purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Arnan de Gans\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2336:\"<p>Earlier today a friend of mine tried to set up <a href=\"http://www.pushover.net\" target=\"_blank\">Pushover</a> for his home automation system and asked for some help in doing so. While exploring the options of it, almost immediately I thought this would be useful for AdRotate as well.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re unfamiliar with Pushover, or push notifications in general; Push notifications are small text-only messages (usually the size of a tweet or smaller) to alert you of certain things or events &#8211;  A new email, new tweet, changed bank balance. Something that needs your attention. These messages are sent to your smartphone and may appear on your lock screen, home screen or in some sort of notification center.<br />\nPushover is a service providing such notifications for pretty much every app/script/service that supports it and sends these notifications to Android and iOS.</p>\n<p>The Pushover API is really cool and allows for a whole bunch of options which can be used for AdRotate <img src=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" />  yay!</p>\n<p>So I&#8217;ve been going over how the email notifications currently work. And how that can be expanded with Push notifications. Here&#8217;s a first draft of the settings that could be in AdRotate on top of the Email notifications already in place &#8211; </p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/pushover.png\" rel=\"lightbox-0\"><img src=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/pushover.png\" alt=\"pushover\" width=\"929\" height=\"637\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-12466\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you have ideas on how this can work for AdRotate, why you (don&#8217;t) like it or anything to make this a great feature for AdRotate please share your ideas in the comments <img src=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\" /> </p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/push-notifications-coming-to-adrotate-pro/\">Push Notifications coming to AdRotate Pro</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com\">AdRotate for WordPress</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/AdrotatePluginForWordpress/~4/9zNRDQhu7uU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/push-notifications-coming-to-adrotate-pro/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://www.adrotateplugin.com/2014/03/push-notifications-coming-to-adrotate-pro/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"Missing menu items for a bunch of sites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0